issue.title: MkDeployKeys - create method is not working correctly.

repository.name: jcabi-github
repository.description: Java Object-Oriented Wrapper of GitHub API, with a fake implementation of the entire GitHub API (for your tests)

issue.body:
I'm working on ticket #343. I saw that create method in MkDeployKeys is not working. 
Example 1:

```
    final DeployKey key = keys.create("Title1", "Key1");
        System.out.println(key.number());  // println 1
        final DeployKey key2 = keys.create("Title2", "Key2");
        System.out.println(key2.number()); // println 1 -- wrong here
```

Expected: `key2.number() != key.number()`

Example 2:

```
    final DeployKey key = keys.create("Title1", "Key1");
        System.out.println(key.json().toString());
```

We got an exception

```
com.jcabi.xml.ListWrapper$NodeNotFoundException: XPath '/repos/jeff/test/deployKeys/deployKey[id=1]' not found in '<?xml version=\\\"1.0\\\" encoding=\\\"UTF-8\\\" standalon..75..ame>\\r\\n</repo>\\r\\n</repos>\\r\\n</github>\\r\\n': Index (0) is out of bounds (size=0)
```
